<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-07T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="36" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee
                                (Arms)/117: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-07T12:00:00-05:00">March
                                        7, 1935—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>480. No. 91 March 5, 6 p.m., from Embassy, London. The objections to
                                inspection on the spot, which Simon set forth in his conversation
                                with Atherton, would appear to be based upon the false assumption
                                that the inspection provided for in the Draft Articles is intended
                                to cover stocks in reserve and arms in possession of the armed
                                forces of the State. Does the British Delegation thoroughly
                                understand that such is not the case and that the inspection
                                provided for covers arms only in the course of manufacture and up to
                                the time of their delivery?</p>
                            <p>Repeat to London.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>